flowRoot.flowPara: Supplementary Figure 5. spacemake readily works with Slide-seqV2 data (A) UMI distribution over the spatial puck. (B) Per-gene corelation of slideseq-tools and spacemake. Red genes are 2-fold enriched in slideseq-tools, while green genes are 2-fold enriched in spacemake. (C) Clustering is able to identify spatially resolved clusters, such as cortical layer, dentate gyrus, pyramidal layer and thalamic region (left panel). Neighborhood-enrichment with squidpy allows to identify clusters which are co-represented in space (cluster 4 and 5). (D) Downsampling analysis reveals low reads/UMIs ratio (right panel), which indicates that this sample has not reached sequencing saturation yet.
